{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"Own transient-failure retries at the httpx transport layer (`AsyncTenacityTransport`) so a mid-agentic-run blip self-heals below the agent graph, without re-executing already-run (side-effecting) tools. Includes a transport-injection spike to de-risk the load-bearing integration point.\n\n## Why\nA transient 429/529/5xx during a tool-using gate op must recover WITHOUT restarting the agent loop — a restart re-posts side-effecting tool calls (ticket comments) and multiplies token cost. The community answer (pydantic-ai retries doc; Anthropic/OpenAI SDKs) is per-request retry at the HTTP transport, which re-sends only the one failed call while completed tool results are untouched. This is the riskiest integration point in the epic, so it is verified by a spike before the rest is built on it.\n\n## What\n- **Dependency:** add the `retries` extra to the existing `[agents]` dep — i.e. spell it `pydantic-ai-slim[anthropic,retries]` (combined extras, alongside the current `pydantic-ai-slim[anthropic]>=1,<2`). `[retries]` is a CONFIRMED extra (present in the installed `pydantic-ai-slim` `Provides-Extra` metadata; reproduce: `python -c \"import importlib.metadata as m; print('retries' in m.metadata('pydantic-ai-slim').get_all('Provides-Extra'))\"` -> `True`) that ships `pydantic_ai.retries.AsyncTenacityTransport` + `wait_retry_after` and pulls in `tenacity` (verified NOT currently installed). Fallback if a future pin ever drops it: add `tenacity` directly. AC verifies `make install` provisions tenacity and the combined-extra spelling resolves cleanly.\n- **Injection covers ALL Anthropic construction paths (not just the loopback bypass):** TODAY a custom `AnthropicProvider(base_url=_direct)` is built ONLY inside the loopback-proxy-bypass branch (`runner.py:238-245`, guarded by `resolved.startswith(\"anthropic\")` AND a non-empty `_direct`); on the normal model-string path pydantic-ai builds its own provider internally, so a naive injection there would give retry coverage ONLY when the headroom proxy is present and silently leave normal runs on the SDK default (2) with no transport. Fix: refactor to a SINGLE Anthropic-model construction that ALWAYS builds `AnthropicModel(name, provider=AnthropicProvider(anthropic_client=AsyncAnthropic(base_url=<_direct or default>, max_retries=0, http_client=<AsyncClient with AsyncTenacityTransport>)))` for any anthropic model — the loopback bypass just varies `base_url`. `AnthropicProvider.__init__` params confirmed at 1.107.0 (`api_key, base_url, anthropic_client, http_client`).\n- **Startup guard (no silent downgrade):** assert at construction that the model was built with our retrying client (transport present, `max_retries==0`); if injection ever fails to apply, FAIL FAST rather than silently regress from today's 2 retries to 0. (`wait_retry_after` verified importable from `pydantic_ai.retries` with signature `(fallback_strategy, max_wait)` — it IS a standalone helper, exactly as the plan assumes; reproduce: `python -c \"from pydantic_ai.retries import wait_retry_after, AsyncTenacityTransport; import inspect; print(list(inspect.signature(wait_retry_after).parameters))\"` -> `['fallback_strategy', 'max_wait']`.) The spike below is the load-bearing proof the custom client is forwarded to the SDK and intercepts responses — do NOT skip it on the signature alone.\n- **Retry set:** `{429, 529, 500, 502, 503, 504}` + `httpx.TimeoutException`/`httpx.ConnectError` via a `validate_response` callback (status codes are not exceptions by default), with `wait_retry_after` (honor `Retry-After`, cap at max_wait), `stop_after_attempt(N)`, `reraise=True`. **Add 529 explicitly** — pydantic-ai's sample list omits it. (`reraise=True` re-raises the last attempt's ORIGINAL exception on the normal exhaustion path; story 30ff's classifier additionally unwraps a `tenacity.RetryError` defensively for the edge paths where tenacity wraps — the two are complementary, not contradictory: reraise is the intended behavior, the unwrap is belt-and-suspenders.)\n- **Spike (de-risk):** an integration test that drives the real `AsyncTenacityTransport` with a mock httpx transport returning `429` (with `Retry-After`) then `200`, asserting the retry happens BELOW the Anthropic SDK, that `Retry-After` is honored, and that a single agent turn sees one successful response.\n- **Streaming out of scope:** the runner uses buffered `agent.run_sync()` (no streaming), so mid-stream partial-byte retry is not applicable; retries operate on whole buffered request/response pairs.\n\n- **Owns the shared httpx.AsyncClient (coordination).** This story CONSTRUCTS the single `httpx.AsyncClient` at `runner.py:238-245` that carries BOTH the `AsyncTenacityTransport` (here) AND the read/tool timeout `httpx.Timeout` (contributed by story fd1d) — one client, two settings, not two competing clients. fd1d passes its `httpx.Timeout` into this construction; this story is the named owner of the client-construction seam so the two configs merge deterministically.\n- **Async-under-run_sync (verified reasoning):** `AsyncTenacityTransport` is async, which is correct — under `agent.run_sync()` pydantic-ai drives the async `AsyncAnthropic` client in an internally-managed event loop, so the async transport on that client is the right layer. The spike confirms it operates under `run_sync`.\n\n## Scope\n- Dependency + transport wiring + shared-client ownership + spike + config keys with concrete defaults: `verify.llm_retry_max_attempts` (default 4), `verify.llm_retry_max_wait_s` (Retry-After / backoff cap, default 60) + docs. **Opt-out / staged rollout:** `verify.llm_retry_max_attempts = 0` disables transport retry (behaves like today's no-app-retry), so the behavioral change has a config toggle, not just a code revert.\n- **Transport-retry-architecture ADR:** the novel decision (retry at the httpx transport with SDK `max_retries=0`, justified by side-effect-safety — already-run tools are not repeated) is captured; the ADR is authored here and RECORDED by story 2eca (sole ADR owner) so future maintainers who consider moving the retry layer find the invariants.\n- Make the ticket-comment tool idempotent (client-generated dedupe key) so a block-then-rerun (or a future resume) can't double-post.\n- NOT in scope: message-history-replay resume (future Tier-2, noted); streaming retry (no streaming used).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `pydantic-ai-slim[retries]` + `tenacity` added to `pyproject.toml`; `make install` provisions them.\n- [ ] The spike integration test proves a `429`(+`Retry-After`)→`200` sequence is retried at the transport layer below the SDK, honoring `Retry-After`, within one agent turn.\n- [ ] Retries owned solely by the transport; SDK `max_retries=0` verified.\n- [ ] 529 + the transient set retried; `Retry-After` honored and capped at `verify.llm_retry_max_wait_s`.\n- [ ] A mid-run transient (injected) self-heals with no tool re-execution: RED case flips GREEN and asserts no duplicate comment.\n- [ ] The comment tool is idempotent on re-run (dedupe-key test).\n- [ ] `make test`/`make lint`/`make typecheck` green.\n\nFiles: `pyproject.toml`, `src/rebar/llm/runner.py`, `src/rebar/config.py`, `src/rebar/_config_schema.py`, the rebar comment-tool surface used by the agentic runner."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783621108431036001,"uuid":"1b705682-653a-4a0b-b019-b2e20e89b0f6"}